	  <concept id="i1094727"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">23.405</ph> Procedures.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1529e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1543e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Designated items and procurement guidelines.</i>
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d1529e26" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1543e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Recovered Materials.</i> Contracting officers should refer to EPA’s list of EPA-designated items (available via the Internet at <xref href="https://www.epa.gov/smm/comprehensive-procurement-guideline-cpg-program#products"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">https://www.epa.gov/smm/comprehensive-procurement-guideline-cpg-program#products</xref>) and to their agencies’ affirmative procurement program when purchasing products that contain recovered material, or services that could include the use of products that contain recovered material.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1543e45" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Biobased products.</i> Contracting officers should refer to USDA’s list of USDA-designated items (available through the Internet at <xref href="http://www.biopreferred.gov"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">http://www.biopreferred.gov</xref>) and to their agencies affirmative procurement program when purchasing supplies that contain biobased material or when purchasing services that could include supplies that contain biobased material.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1543e60" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                When acquiring recovered material or biobased products, the contracting officer may request information or data on such products, including recycled or biobased content or related standards of the products (see <xref href="FAR-i1114209.dita#i1114209"
                              base="i1114209"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">11.302</xref>(c)).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1543e74" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Procurement exemptions.</i>
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d1529e80" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1543e87" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Once an item has been designated by either EPA or USDA, agencies shall purchase conforming products unless an exemption applies (see <xref href="FAR-i1094692.dita#i1094692"
                              base="i1094692"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">23.404</xref>(b)).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1543e99" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                When an exemption is used for an EPA-designated item or the procurement of a product containing recovered material does not meet or exceed the EPA recovered material content guidelines, the contracting officer shall place a written justification in the contract file.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1543e110" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
						            <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Program priorities.</i> When both the USDA-designated item and the EPA-designated item will be used for the same purposes, and both meet the agency’s needs, the agency shall purchase the EPA-designated item.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
